                <expan><abbr>A</abbr><ex>ulo</ex></expan> Barbio <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>A</abbr><ex>uli</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilio</ex></expan> Grato <expan><abbr>Vel</abbr><ex>ina</ex></expan> &amp;lt;a&amp;gt;<expan><abbr>n<am>n</am></abbr><ex>orum</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/>LXXV et Comi<lb break="no" n="4"/><expan><abbr>nia</abbr><ex>e</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>iti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>iliae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Pupa</abbr><ex>e</ex></expan> <lb n="5"/><expan><abbr>n<am>n</am></abbr><ex>orum</ex></expan> LXX <expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>ito</ex></expan> Barb<lb break="no" n="6"/>io <expan><abbr>A</abbr><ex>uli</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilio</ex></expan> Quinto <lb n="7"/><expan><abbr>mil</abbr><ex>iti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>leg</abbr><ex>ionis</ex></expan> XV <expan><abbr>Apo</abbr><ex>llinaris</ex></expan> <lb n="8"/><expan><abbr>n<am>n</am></abbr><ex>orum</ex></expan> XXV <expan><abbr>h</abbr><ex>ic</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>iti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>unt</ex></expan> <lb n="9"/><expan><abbr>A</abbr><ex>ulus</ex></expan> Barbius Adiutor <lb n="10"/><expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucius</ex></expan> Barbius Iustus <lb n="11"/><expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aius</ex></expan> Barbius Aptus <lb n="12"/>Barbia Tertia Barbia <lb n="13"/>Hospita Barbia <lb n="14"/>Satul<expan><ex>l</ex><abbr>a</abbr></expan> Barbia <lb n="15"/>Lucia <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilii</ex></expan> et filiae <lb n="16"/><expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex cert="low">ro</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex cert="low">ietate</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Material: möglicherweise thasischer Marmor. Im Giebel oberhalb des Inschriftfeldes Gorgoneion, in den Zwickeln darüber Delphine; unterhalb des Inschriftfeldes zwei Trauergenien. Z. 2 (Ende): NN-Ligatur; Querhaste des damit ligiert gedachten A nicht angegeben (also wohl nur aufgemalt) oder vielleicht ehemals nur sehr schwach eingeritzt. (B): CIL III 5680: ILLPRON: Z. 11: G(aius)</p>
            </div>
